CREATED:20251125T211428Z
DESCRIPTION:Experience the warmth and artistry of the Ciompi Quartet in th
 is midday installment of their popular Ciompi on West series-an ongoing i
 nitiative that brings exceptional chamber music to diverse and unexpected
  spaces across Duke's campus. Held in the serene and acoustically rich Go
 odson Chapel\, this informal concert invites listeners to enjoy world-cla
 ss performance in a setting that encourages reflection\, connection\, and
  close listening.\n\nThe Ciompi Quartet\, long admired for their expressi
 ve depth and collaborative spirit\, is joined by talented student ensembl
 es from the Chamber Music at Duke program\, who help round out this vibra
 nt one-hour program. Together\, they offer a mix of repertoire that highl
 ights the breadth and vitality of Duke's chamber music community-from stu
 dent-driven interpretations to the quartet's seasoned artistry.\n\nWhethe
 r you're stopping by between classes\, taking a midday break\, or simply 
 seeking a moment of beauty on West Campus\, Ciompi on West provides a wel
 coming space to experience live chamber music in a relaxed and inspiring 
 atmosphere.\n\nFree and open to the public. All are welcome.
DURATION:PT1H30M
DTSTAMP:20251125T211428Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260410T120000
LAST-MODIFIED:20251125T211428Z
