DESCRIPTION:A group of characters interrupt a rehearsal\, claiming to be u
 nfinished creations of an author who abandoned them. They demand to have 
 their story told\, confronting the nature of reality\, illusion\, and the
  relationship between art and life. Theater Studies faculty and playwrigh
 t Neal Bell adapts the absurdist metatheatrical drama by Luigi Pirandello
 . Sound Design by Ethan Eldred and Costume Design by Hannah Haverkamp.
DURATION:PT2H
